{"art": [], "author": [{"email_address": "immigration@politifact.com", "first_name": "Miriam", "id": 586, "last_name": "Valverde", "name_slug": "miriam-valverde", "on_staff_page": 11, "phone": "617-396-7423", "photo": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/politifact/staffers/zwPolitifactHeadshots19.JPG", "publication": {"id": 1, "publication_name": "PolitiFact", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/publication/1/"}, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/staffer/586/", "title": "Staff writer", "twitter": "MiriamValverde"}], "canonical_url": "/punditfact/statements/2018/aug/15/blog-posting/no-kevin-bacon-did-not-say-we-are-blessed-have-don/", "edition": {"adkey": "Editions", "advalue": "Punditfact", "edition": "PunditFact", "edition_slug": "punditfact", "has_afterthefact": false, "id": 48, "index_page": false, "meter_name": "The PunditFact Truth-O-Meter", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/edition/48/"}, "editor": [{"email_address": "ksanders@poynter.org", "first_name": "Katie", "id": 231, "last_name": "Sanders", "name_slug": "katie-sanders", "on_staff_page": 3, "phone": "727-553-4667", "photo": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/politifact/staffers/zwPolitifactHeadshots09.JPG", "publication": {"id": 1, "publication_name": "PolitiFact", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/publication/1/"}, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/staffer/231/", "title": "Managing Editor", "twitter": "KatieLSanders"}], "facebook_headline": "No, Kevin Bacon did not praise Donald Trump", "id": 15736, "in_future": false, "is_pundit": false, "make_public": true, "preview": true, "researcher": [{"email_address": "immigration@politifact.com", "first_name": "Miriam", "id": 586, "last_name": "Valverde", "name_slug": "miriam-valverde", "on_staff_page": 11, "phone": "617-396-7423", "photo": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/politifact/staffers/zwPolitifactHeadshots19.JPG", "publication": {"id": 1, "publication_name": "PolitiFact", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/publication/1/"}, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/staffer/586/", "title": "Staff writer", "twitter": "MiriamValverde"}], "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/statement/15736/", "ruling": {"adkey": "Truth-O-Meter", "advalue": "Pants on Fire", "id": 6, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/statementruling/6/", "ruling": "Pants on Fire!", "ruling_graphic": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/rulings/tom-pantsonfire.gif", "ruling_slug": "pants-fire"}, "ruling_comments": "<p>Actor Kevin Bacon did not say &quot;we are blessed&quot; to have Donald Trump as president. That&rsquo;s a made-up story resurfacing on social media.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>An obscure website called Phoenix Post published <a href=\"https://www.phoenixpost.site/video-kevin-bacon-saying-we-are-blessed-to-have-donald-trump-as-our-president/\">a story Aug. 14 </a>headlined, &quot;VIDEO Kevin Bacon Saying &lsquo;We Are Blessed To Have Donald Trump As Our President&rsquo;.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But there&rsquo;s no video of Bacon saying that. This story was flagged as part of Facebook&rsquo;s efforts to combat false news and misinformation on its News Feed. (Read more about our <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/help/1952307158131536?helpref=related\">partnership with Facebook</a>.)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://makeamericagreatforever.blogspot.com/2018/07/video-kevin-bacon-saying-we-are-blessed.html\">The false</a> <a href=\"http://trumpfriends.tk/kevin-bacon-we-are-blessed-to-have-donald-trump-as-our-president-he-is-the-only-one-who-can/\">story</a> has been around for months on other websites. Bacon in December 2017 <a href=\"https://twitter.com/kevinbacon/status/937797579189956608\">tweeted</a> a link to a <a href=\"https://www.gossipcop.com/kevin-bacon-donald-trump-president-blessed/\">Gossip Cop story</a> debunking the narrative. &quot;Wow. Thanks for clearing this up,&quot; Bacon wrote in the tweet.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"artembed\">See Figure 1 on PolitiFact.com</div>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://twitter.com/kevinbacon/status/937832960128102400?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw%7Ctwcamp%5Etweetembed%7Ctwterm%5E937832960128102400&amp;ref_url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.factcheck.org%2F2017%2F12%2Fkevin-bacon-isnt-trump-supporter%2F\">Bacon went</a> further in a separate December tweet, saying there was nothing about Trump&rsquo;s policies &quot;that I agree with. And nothing about his character that I admire.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"artembed\">See Figure 2 on PolitiFact.com</div>\r\n\r\n<p>Phoenix Post claimed Bacon&rsquo;s praise for Trump came during an interview on ABC&rsquo;s This Week. But the Gossip Cop story shared by Bacon noted that the actor hadn&rsquo;t been on the ABC show <a href=\"https://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/kevin-bacon/credits/160550/\">since 2007</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Phoenix Post&rsquo;s headline explicitly says &quot;Kevin Bacon,&quot; but the text of the story replaced his last name with &quot;publisher 1st baron verulam,&quot; or &quot;1st Baron Verulam&quot; (apparently trying to reference a title given to the philosopher <a href=\"https://www.britannica.com/biography/Francis-Bacon-Viscount-Saint-Alban\">Francis </a><a href=\"https://www.fbrt.org.uk/pages/bacon.html\">Bacon</a>).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>PunditFact has fact-checked <a href=\"https://www.politifact.com/subjects/fake-news/\">multiple hoaxes</a> about celebrities praising Trump, including these involving <a href=\"https://www.politifact.com/punditfact/statements/2018/apr/24/blog-posting/no-denzel-washington-didnt-praise-trump-averting-w/\">Denzel Washington</a>, <a href=\"https://www.politifact.com/punditfact/statements/2018/apr/09/politics-elite-trump/fake-news-claims-emma-stone-converted-trump-suppor/\">Emma Stone</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.politifact.com/punditfact/statements/2018/mar/12/universal-news-portal/headline-jennifer-aniston-formed-celebrities-trump/\">Jennifer Aniston</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bacon did not say &quot;we are blessed to have Donald Trump as our president.&quot; We rate that fabricated story as Pants on Fire!</p>\r\n\r\n<div class='artembed'>See Figure 3 on PolitiFact.com</div>\r\n", "ruling_comments_date": "2018-08-15T13:24:18.099684", "ruling_date": "2018-08-15T13:37:37", "ruling_headline": "No, Kevin Bacon did not say 'we are blessed' to have Donald Trump as president", "ruling_headline_slug": "no-kevin-bacon-did-not-say-we-are-blessed-have-don", "ruling_link_text": "He didn't say that", "ruling_state": null, "source_documents": null, "sources": "<p>Phoenix Post, <a href=\"https://www.phoenixpost.site/video-kevin-bacon-saying-we-are-blessed-to-have-donald-trump-as-our-president/\">VIDEO Kevin Bacon Saying &lsquo;We Are Blessed To Have Donald Trump As Our President&rsquo;</a>, Aug. 14, 2018</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Gossipcop.com, <a href=\"https://www.gossipcop.com/kevin-bacon-donald-trump-president-blessed/\">Kevin&nbsp;Bacon Did NOT Say &quot;We Are Blessed To Have Donald Trump As President,&quot; Despite Report</a>, Dec. 4, 2017</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Brittanica.com,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.britannica.com/biography/Francis-Bacon-Viscount-Saint-Alban\">Francis Bacon</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Francis Bacon Research Trust, <a href=\"https://www.fbrt.org.uk/pages/bacon.html\">Bacon</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>TVGuide.com, <a href=\"https://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/kevin-bacon/credits/160550/\">Kevin Bacon</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Twitter, @KevinBacon <a href=\"https://twitter.com/kevinbacon/status/937797579189956608\">tweet</a>, <a href=\"https://twitter.com/kevinbacon/status/937832960128102400?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw%7Ctwcamp%5Etweetembed%7Ctwterm%5E937832960128102400&amp;ref_url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.factcheck.org%2F2017%2F12%2Fkevin-bacon-isnt-trump-supporter%2F\">tweet</a>, Dec. 4, 2017</p>\r\n", "speaker": {"adkey": null, "advalue": null, "barely_true_count": 26, "current_job": "", "false_count": 87, "first_name": "", "half_true_count": 15, "home_state": "", "id": 43, "last_name": "Bloggers", "mostly_true_count": 10, "name_slug": "blog-posting", "pants_count": 279, "party": {"id": 2, "party": "None", "party_slug": "none", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/party/2/"}, "photo": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/mugs/mug-bloggers.jpg", "primary_edition": {"adkey": "Editions", "advalue": "Punditfact", "edition": "PunditFact", "edition_slug": "punditfact", "has_afterthefact": false, "id": 48, "index_page": false, "meter_name": "The PunditFact Truth-O-Meter", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/edition/48/"}, "promise_meter_cutout": null, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/person/43/", "total_count": 425, "true_count": 5, "website": ""}, "statement": "<p>&quot;VIDEO Kevin Bacon Saying &lsquo;We Are Blessed To Have Donald Trump As Our President&rsquo;&quot;</p>\r\n", "statement_context": "a blog post", "statement_date": "2018-08-14", "statement_type": {"id": 2, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/statementtype/2/", "statement_type": "Claim", "type_description": "blog post "}, "subject": [{"description": "<p>There&rsquo;s an interesting discussion happening now about the spread of fake news on the Internet and what companies like Facebook, Google and Twitter, among others, should do to stop it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>That&rsquo;s a healthy conversation to have, and one we hope continues in the weeks and months ahead.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But that doesn&rsquo;t mean we can&rsquo;t do something now. Here at PolitiFact, we&rsquo;re beefing up our coverage of fake news to help our readers better sort out fact from fiction on their social media feeds.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The claims can be about anything -- politics, entertainment, a fishy-sounding medical cure.</p>\r\n", "id": 323, "photo": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/subjects/mugs/fake.png", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/subject/323/", "subject": "Fake news", "subject_slug": "fake-news", "used_in_edition": ["/api/v/2/edition/56/", "/api/v/2/edition/49/", "/api/v/2/edition/53/", "/api/v/2/edition/4/", "/api/v/2/edition/5/", "/api/v/2/edition/60/", "/api/v/2/edition/61/", "/api/v/2/edition/50/", "/api/v/2/edition/51/", "/api/v/2/edition/1/", "/api/v/2/edition/59/", "/api/v/2/edition/57/", "/api/v/2/edition/47/", "/api/v/2/edition/13/", "/api/v/2/edition/55/", "/api/v/2/edition/58/", "/api/v/2/edition/7/", "/api/v/2/edition/9/", "/api/v/2/edition/54/", "/api/v/2/edition/48/", "/api/v/2/edition/6/", "/api/v/2/edition/14/", "/api/v/2/edition/2/", "/api/v/2/edition/10/", "/api/v/2/edition/8/"]}], "target": [], "twitter_headline": "No, @KevinBacon did not say 'we are blessed' to have @realdonaldtrump as president"}